item.title: Dungeoneering Master Cape Emote Error
item.dc:creator: @Team_Rocket Team_Rocket
item.description:
@Team_Rocket wrote:

Yes, this is most likely caused by missing or too many ‘Curly Brackets’.

Missing "}" "{" Brackets

This is a common programming error in any programming language and can be eradicated by means of a proper indentation scheme.

A good rule of thumb, is to remember that you must close out a Method with each Bracket corresponding to opposite Brackets. Counting Brackets is a good start, and eventually you will move on to an Integrated Developmental Environment, which is capable of doing this for you.

P.S. The practice of Conventions and organizational habits will help to prevent problems such as this.
